          <aside class="notes">
            Starting in the late 1980s an explosion of general purpose computers has enabled digital transformation of businesses. Dedicated mainframe computer facilities evolved and extended their footprint to accommodate racks of general purpose server hardware. New data centres have continued to evolve and optimise efficiency. Due to the enormous cost of building and refurbishing data centres there is a continuum of capability and efficiency. Data centres are energy-hungry buildings: a small one may draw 10MW of power and a large one can draw 100MW or more.
